    • Class goal.core.program.Module extends ParsedObject implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      6847272337331077937L

      • Serialized Fields

        • name

          java.lang.String name
          Identifier for this Module.

          The identifier 'name' should define a unique ID in combination with the number of parameters 'nr' of this module. I.e. 'name/nr' should be unique. ModuleValidator checks whether this is actually the case.

          The following names are reserved and used for built-in module types:

          • init
          • main
          • event

        • parameters

          java.util.List<E> parameters
          The parameters of this Module. The parameter list may be empty.

        • type

          Module.TYPE type
          The Module.TYPE of this Module.

        • ruleSet

          RuleSet ruleSet
          The set of Rules of this Module. Initializes rule evaluation order by default to linear.

          These are obtained by parsing the program section of a module in an agent program.

        • entrychannel

          Channel entrychannel
          Channel to report the entry of this Module on. Should be null for anonymous modules (and no reports should be generated).

        • exitchannel

          Channel exitchannel
          Channel to report the exit of this Module on. Should be null for anonymous modules (and no reports should be generated).

        • isUsed

          boolean isUsed
          Mark module by default as unused. ActionComboValidator should set this flag to true if the module is used in the program (except for the built-in modules init, main, and event which are always used). Anonymous modules are also always used.

        • result

          Result result
          The last result of an execute-call

    • Class goal.core.program.literals.MentalStateCond extends ParsedObject implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      2588480710614917621L

      • Serialized Fields

        • formulas

          java.util.List<E> formulas
          A MentalStateCond is defined in terms of a list of MentalFormulas. Mental formulas are used here to be able to define an MSC in terms of both MentalLiterals as well as Macros. So MentalStateCond.formulas stores the original definition of this MentalStateCond but should only be used if this original definition is needed for presentation purposes. For al other purposes, use MentalStateCond.literals.

        • literals

          java.util.List<E> literals
          A mental state condition effectively is a conjunction of MentalLiterals. All mental literals are collected (e.g. from Macro's that occur in the condition) and put in a list when MentalStateCond.getLiterals() is called for the first time.

        • latest

          java.util.Set<E> latest

        • preassignedElementIndex

          java.util.List<E> preassignedElementIndex
          dsingh, Sep 10, 2013: The lists below are used to store preassigned indices for elements. Any new element added to the universe is checked against this array and if a match is found (string match) then the index of that element in this array will be used. Preassigned indices are used during learning only and should not interfere with normal operation when preassignedElementIndex should always be null. Ideally we would want to do this by simply serializing this object, but since that is not possible, we use this scheme.
